0） For general run:
 git clone https://github.com/we1yuan/lab3.git "your folder name lab3 defaut"
 javac *.java
Terminal 1：
 java Server
Terminal 2:
 java Client

1) creat network namespaces and veth (network namespaces):

sudo ip netns add ns-server
sudo ip netns add ns-client

sudo ip link add veth-server type veth peer name veth-client

sudo ip link set veth-server netns ns-server
sudo ip link set veth-client netns ns-client

sudo ip -n ns-server addr add 10.0.0.1/24 dev veth-server
sudo ip -n ns-client addr add 10.0.0.2/24 dev veth-client

sudo ip -n ns-server link set lo up
sudo ip -n ns-client link set lo up
sudo ip -n ns-server link set veth-server up
sudo ip -n ns-client link set veth-client up

 2) standar case without delay or loss

Terminal 1：
sudo ip netns exec ns-server java Server


Terminal 2：
printf "10.0.0.1\n8080\ntest.txt\n128\n" | sudo ip netns exec ns-client java Client

check result：
cmp test.txt output.txt && echo "FILES MATCH"

 3)  Delay senario


sudo ip netns exec ns-server tc qdisc add dev veth-server root netem delay 1000ms 20ms distribution normal
sudo ip netns exec ns-client tc qdisc add dev veth-client root netem delay 1000ms 20ms distribution normal

Terminal 1：
sudo ip netns exec ns-server java Server

Terminal 2：
printf "10.0.0.1\n8080\ntest.txt\n128\n" | sudo ip netns exec ns-client java Client


 4)  Loss senario

DELETE the delay qdisc:
sudo ip netns exec ns-server tc qdisc del dev veth-server root
sudo ip netns exec ns-client tc qdisc del dev veth-client root

// 15% packet loss senario:
sudo ip netns exec ns-server tc qdisc replace dev veth-server root netem loss random 15%
sudo ip netns exec ns-client tc qdisc replace dev veth-client root netem loss random 15%


Terminal 1：
sudo ip netns exec ns-server java Server

Terminal 2：
printf "10.0.0.1\n8080\ntest.txt\n128\n" | sudo ip netns exec ns-client java Client

 
 5)

DELETE all:

sudo ip netns exec ns-server tc qdisc del dev veth-server root
sudo ip netns exec ns-client tc qdisc del dev veth-client root

sudo ip netns del ns-server
sudo ip netns del ns-client
